This paper involves the use of tactile sensing in robotics, which is a key area of research in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also uses data-driven methods to infer object properties, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of hidden Markov models (HMMs) is a common machine learning technique, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the analysis of time-varying tactile sensor data, which could fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper involves the testing of the method on different robot motions, which could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
